HEADWORD: Parure
<hw>Pa`rure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., OF.
<ets>pareure</ets>, LL. <ets>paraura</ets>, fr. L. <ets>parare</ets> to
prepare. See <er>Pare</er>.]</ety> <def>An ornament or decoration for
the person; esp., a decoration consisting of a set of ornaments to be
used together; <as>as, a <ex>parure</ex> of rubies or of
embroideries</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parus</ent>⟦br⟧
